summary: Commission Status
title: Commission Status
body:
The pineapple quilt for my Twitter client is at the 50% finished point for the hand-quilting.  I was hoping to have finished by tomorrow, but alas, it was not meant to be.  Perhaps next Sunday.

The gem of the heart quilt mat for my DeviantArt client is at 0%.  I’ve yet to receive color choices.

After I finish these I’ll accept only very small and quick commissions, and will open up for large ones in six to eight months.  There are personal projects I want to work on, and these will help prevent burnout.

  1. My Mom’s place mat set (likely to have it done by Mother’s Day)
  2. My middle sister’s place mat set, which I’ve only picked out fabrics and a pattern thus far.  I’ll start that set when I finish my mom’s.
  3. An altar mat for myself.
  4. Various small table runners and mats for swaps on swap-bot.com.
  5. Table runner with matching place mats for my dining room.
  6. A lap quilt for my husband.
  7. Two giveaway quilts.  One will be nearly large enough for a twin size bed, the other a lap quilt.  All the blocks were received via swap-bot.com, leaving me only to sew them into a quilt top, followed by hand-quilting.  I want the smaller of the two finished by June for the Spring/Summer giveaway, and the larger on for the Fall/Winter giveaway. 

It’s a lot, but it’s fun.  Commissions can be fun, but I have limited artistic freedom.  Not always bad, but I wanna play for a bit.  I think any artist who accepts commissions understands this.

If you’ve been wanting to commission me for some time now, you have several more months to save up for that 50% upfront payment and the 50% + shipping payment after the project is finished. 

Ideally, I’d rather see what I have listed on Etsy sell first.  I’m running out of places to hang the quilts away from the kitties!  Use coupon code SPRINGBACK for 25% off a purchase of $100+.  I ship internationally!

My Etsy Shop: https://www.etsy.com/shop/CreationsByChaosfay

If you’d rather support me without purchasing anything from my shop I do have options set up for that.

My Ko-Fi: https://ko-fi.com/chaosfay

My CashApp: $Chaosfay

My Venmo: Chaosfay

Thank you for taking the time to read this.  I really appreciate it.  BTW, you are welcomed to reblog this as well.

summary: Tempo al tempo
body:
Tempo al tempo

Ehy fratè, tutto questo un giorno passerà sai? Forse non dovrei dirti queste cose, ma la vita è una, il tempo scorre e non fa sconti a nessuno e in più tu sei molto fragile. Il mio tempo è sempre andato più veloce degli altri,nel bene o nel male. Penso che infondo sono solo,e che anche il tempo,pur di non rimanere con me, si divincola e cerca di scappare dalle mie mani,come hai fatto anche tu. Io non lo biasimo,io sono noioso,delle volte non so neanche cosa dire agli altri, cercare di mandare avanti un discorso anche quando non vorrei, eppure nella mente delle persone sono uno di quelli che fa la differenza quando manca,forse è sempre stata una mia qualità. E che non so cosa pensare che tutto questo è cosi monotono,la provincia è noiosa, sto per esaurire tutte le mie cartuccie e sinceramente voglio allontanarmi. Qualcuno ha detto che la mente è una prigione, ed ha ragione. Non voglio sprecare il mio tempo, voglio vivere il più possibile perchè me lo merito,cazzo. Sono Gianpaolo, non un “tipo” di persona, non so catalogarmi ( e non voglio) io, figuratevi se potete farlo voi. Fratè questi ricordi me li porterò fino alla fine,fino alla fine.

“…I have some concerns…”

“D'aw, you look gorgeous, darling!”

Based on some doodles and ideas bounced around with @alanatedmon. Sona wants to be more “lady like” and started to take tips from Yadei (down to even studying how she drinks wine). Yadei decided to roll with this and wanted to try to see if she could introduce Sona to other clothes that aren’t just spandex. I don’t think she likes it.
